<paragraph blockId="6.[824,1477,983,1103]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[862,919,984,1007]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Notes</emphasis>
. – This rare aquatic high Andean species was first detected by Allioni in the páramo of Matanga, in the province of 
<collectingRegion box="[905,973,1047,1071]" country="Ecuador" name="Azuay" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Azuay</collectingRegion>
. The species has usually been called 
<taxonomicName authority="Herzog" authorityName="Herzog" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Balantiopsidaceae" genus="Isotachis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="lacustris">
<emphasis box="[1368,1474,1047,1071]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">I. lacustris</emphasis>
Herzog
</taxonomicName>
, which is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[1150,1232,1079,1103]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Balantiopsidaceae" genus="Isotachis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="obtusa">
<emphasis box="[1150,1232,1079,1103]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">I. obtusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(GRADSTEIN, in press).
</paragraph>
